tip.text: Authentic Vietnamese food that's reasonably priced. There's an indoor air-conditioned seating area as well as an al-fresco dining area outside if you're a smoker.
Their beef horfun is famous. As for the dimsum, it is pretty average.
Claypot bak kut teh and the tze cha here are the only things you need to order.
Cheap and good food here! Try the authentic Thai food from Toi Thai Kitchen, you won't regret it!
$6 for a huge, crispy and yummy murtabak. Shiok!
